# Trimma button contrast (global)

Use `@/components/ui/button` variants — never one-off button colors.

## Contract

| Fill | Text | Hover text | Hover fill |
|------|------|------------|------------|
| Yellow `#ffde5a` (`variant="default"`) | Black `#000` | Black | Lighter yellow `#ffe680` |
| Black / dark (`variant="dark"`) | White `#fff` | Brand yellow `#ffde5a` | Stay black |

## Implementation

- **Yellow CTAs**: `<Button variant="default">` or `buttonVariants({ variant: "default" })` on links.
- **Dark CTAs**: `<Button variant="dark">` or `trimmaDarkBtnClass` from `@/lib/customer-dashboard-ui` (re-exports global `dark` variant).
- **Filter tabs**: `trimmaFilterTabClass(active)` + `.trimma-filter-tab` CSS — do not invent new tab styles.
- Global safeguards live in `apps/web/src/index.css` (dark hover → yellow text; solid yellow → black text).

## Do not

- Add `trimma-customer-btn` or page-specific button color classes.
- Put white text on solid yellow buttons or dark text on solid black buttons.
- Override hover to white text on dark buttons.

## Mobile

- Interactive controls: minimum **44px** touch height on mobile (`min-h-11` or global `.trimma-customer-dashboard` rules).
- Header CTAs: `w-full sm:w-auto` on narrow viewports.
